<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ881004-0103 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief -- General Automation Inc.: Firm Posts $8.9 Million Loss For Fiscal Fourth Quarter </HL><SO> </SO><CO> GA </CO><IN> ERN </IN><TEXT>   General Automation Inc. said write-offs totaling about $8 million contributed to a fiscal fourth-quarter net loss of $8.9 million on revenue of $13.9 million.    The computer systems supplier said it understood auditors &quot;may express . . . concern regarding the company's financial viability unless additional capital is obtained.&quot; The accountant's opinion for the fiscal year, ended June 30, isn't ready.    The write-offs included assets and technology for a computer subsidiary, costs attributable to reorganization by new management and costs relating to settlement of lawsuits. The Anaheim, Calif.-based company in the year-earlier quarter had net income of $1.3 million, or 21 cents a share, on revenue of $13.1 million.    For the fiscal year, General Automation had a net loss of $11 million on revenue of $50.9 million. That compares with net income of $1.6 million, or 33 cents a share, on revenue of $42.8 million a year earlier. </TEXT></DOC>